<br>
For one..if the little yapper is disturbing the peace &lt;several towns have a no bark rule here&gt; and someone does feel there is concern for the dog's well being ..damn right they should call the SPCA &lt;they know the diff between an abuse/neglect case and a spoilt dog just wanting attention&gt;..that's what it's there for..as far as telling the owner first..what the hell for..person is either deaf and won't hear ya knocking at the door or does'nt give a shit and will tell you to go get fucked, either way you are under no obligation to listen to it 24/7. <br>
<br>
However..if the person is elderly i would be down there in a heart beat offering to help exercise the dog for them and maybe babysit every now and then..might even be a person that works all day too..crap..i'm making excuses for them now.<br>
I just hate to see a companion animal left alone when they should be snuggled up on someones lap <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Now let's get to the good stuff...my dogs. I have 2 large male german sheperds, 1 female, 1 male maremma &lt;italian livestock guard dog&gt;, 1 female lab mix, and 1 pomerainian. They are all house dogs..but if i was to go outside, underwater, on an iceberg, side of a valcano..or up an elephants ass to sleep they would be there..why..because i'm mom and we're a pack.<br>
<br>
Because of the fact that i do not believe it's in OUR dogs best interest i do not tie them out..i worked damn hard to fence in 4 acres of our property so the lil shits can all burst out the door all at once in the morning and terrorize any living thing that might be in their path..they have a beaten down trail they run everytime they are released, than they come back and wait by the door to be let in so they can lay in every available inch of space within a six foot radius around where ever the hell i'm sitting.<br>
<br>
They don't need a dog house cause i live in one..as far as other dogs living outside..hell yah..most working and herding dogs do..not ours..but most do and they would be misrable and drive ya nuts if you brought them inside.<br>
<br>
I just love the hell outta my dogs..they are deceint folk..we can let the rats out with them and the freaken cockatiel we have will chase them away from their bowls..our cat will wait outside along with them to be let back in and my daughter who is the same age as 4 &lt;they are all 8 yrs old now&gt;, was raised on the floor along with them &lt;all you ppl that get rid of animals because you're going to have a baby...you suck, whoever tells you ya should, they suck&gt;.<br>
<br>
We either have or have had our dogs around sheep, goats, chickens, geese, turkies, moose, deer,..etc... i have seen the geese attack them time after time and the dogs react with lil more than a hold on the neck..not a bite but a hold like they would use to dicipline a pup..half the time i would like to kill the geese myself, we also had a 40#+ pet turkey that would steal their toys than they would bark their fool heads off till i went outside to retrieve it &lt;which sucked cause the turkey would go right back over and steal it again no matter how far he had to chase them&gt;.<br>
<br>
Every now and then i do see a look come across their faces just before they launch into a game of &quot;Let's see how many times we can chase the goat around the house before it collaspes.&quot; so they are not perfect angles and do need a watchful eye like kids.<br>
<br>
My pom is a pretty cool shit too..she's a chicken herder..don't laugh..impressive as hell watching her drive baby chicks outta the brush pile into my hands..she's also an inside dog..you need a freaken spatula to pry her ass off the bed in the morning.<br>
<br>
Oh well...i could go on forever..suffice to say most of you would'nt even want to sit on my furniture..erm..i mean the dogs furniture, eat my food &lt;just does'nt seem right if there's no dog hair in it&gt; or try to have a conversation with me at the gate..lol..but..i bet ya dog would love me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
